# {{projectName}}

A ready-to-run **Playwright + TypeScript** test automation framework for **web and API** testing, with a **Page Object Model** structure, **{{reporter}}** reporting, and CI wired up out of the box.

Generated by QA Prism. Clone it, install, and you're writing tests in minutes.

---

## Prerequisites

- **Node.js 18 or newer** — check with `node -v`. [Download here](https://nodejs.org).
- **Java 8 or newer** — only needed if you chose Allure reporting. Check with `java -version`.

---

## Setup (3 steps)

```bash
npm install              # 1. install dependencies
npm run install:browsers # 2. install the browsers Playwright drives
cp .env.example .env     # 3. create your local environment file
```

Open `.env` and set your application URLs:

```
WEB_BASE_URL={{webBaseUrl}}
API_BASE_URL={{apiBaseUrl}}
```

---

## Running tests

```bash
npm test            # everything (web + API, all browsers)
npm run test:web    # web only
npm run test:api    # API only
npm run test:headed # watch the browser
npm run test:ui     # interactive UI mode (great for debugging)
npm run test:debug  # step-through debugger
```

Single file: `npx playwright test tests/web/home.spec.ts`

---

## Viewing reports

```bash
npm run report:allure   # rich Allure report (if Allure was selected)
npm run report:html     # Playwright's built-in HTML report
```

