## Project structure

```
{{projectName}}/
├── src/
│   ├── pages/      Page objects (POM) — BasePage + examples
│   ├── api/        Reusable typed API client
│   ├── fixtures/   Auto-inject page objects + API client
│   └── utils/      Centralised test data
├── tests/
│   ├── web/        Web specs
│   └── api/        API specs
├── .github/workflows/  CI pipeline
└── playwright.config.ts
```

---

## Writing your first test

1. Add a page object in `src/pages/` extending `BasePage`.
2. Expose it as a fixture in `src/fixtures/test-fixtures.ts`.
3. Write the test using that fixture — no raw selectors in test files.

Full walkthrough and conventions are in the QA Prism docs.

---

## Conventions

- Always use page objects — never put selectors in test files.
- Prefer role/label/text locators over XPath.
- Keep test data in `src/utils/testData.ts`.
- No hardcoded waits — rely on Playwright auto-waiting.

